      <text bytes="588" xml:space="preserve">{{short description|teletraffic period}}
In [[telecommunication]], '''performance measurement period''' is the period during which performance parameters are measured.  

A performance measurement period is determined by required confidence limits and may vary as a function of the observed parameter values. [[User (telecommunications)|User]] [[time]] is divided into consecutive performance measurement periods to enable measurement of user [[information transfer]] [[Reliability engineering|reliability]].

