      <text bytes="786" xml:space="preserve">{{Refimprove|date=March 2008}}
In [[telecommunication]], a '''periscope antenna''' is an [[antenna (electronics)|antenna]] configuration in which the transmitting antenna is oriented to produce a vertical [[radiation pattern]], and a flat or off-axis [[parabolic reflector]], mounted above the transmitting antenna, is used to direct the [[wikt:beam|beam]] in a horizontal [[Course (navigation)|path]] toward the receiving antenna.  

A periscope antenna facilitates increased terrain clearance without long [[transmission line]]s, while permitting the active equipment to be located at or near ground level for ease of [[repair and maintenance|maintenance]].

