      <text bytes="1051" xml:space="preserve">In [[Universal Personal Telecommunications]] (UPT), '''personal mobility''' is the ability of a [[user (telecommunications)|user]] to access telecommunication services at any UPT [[terminal (telecommunication)|terminal]] on the basis of a personal [[identifier]], and the capability of the [[telecommunications network|network]] to provide those services in accord with the user's [[Universal Personal Telecommunications#UPT service profile|service profile]]. 

Personal mobility involves the network's capability to locate the terminal associated with the user for the purposes of addressing, [[routing]], and charging the user for calls. &quot;Access&quot; is intended to convey the concepts of both originating and terminating services. Management of the service profile by the user is not part of personal mobility. The personal mobility aspects of personal [[telecommunication|communication]]s are based on the [[Universal Personal Telecommunications#UPT number|UPT number]].

